net.sf.jclec.mo.command

Class NonDominatedSolutionsExtractor

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sf.jclec.mo.command.Command
      • net.sf.jclec.mo.command.NonDominatedSolutionsExtractor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, net.sf.jclec.IConfigure, net.sf.jclec.JCLEC
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    NonDominatedFeasibleSolutionsExtractor

    public class NonDominatedSolutionsExtractor
extends Command
    This command extracts the non-dominated solutions of the given population. It requires the definition of the dominance principle to be used. Here, any comparator inheriting from ParetoComparator can be used. The given population is not modified during the execution of the command, since the set of non-dominated solutions is stored in a specific list that can be retrieved using the getNonDominatedSolutions method.

    HISTORY:

    • (AR|JRR|SV, 1.0, March 2018) First release.
